<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7271> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7271" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor? 43. The phrase in Cic. Att. 16.14.4, to the effect that Cicero's nephew Quintus was intending ex Nonis iis quibus nos magna gessimus aedem Opis explicaturum, idque ad populum, indicates that he was then (November 12, 44) expecting to enter office as quaestor on December 5. See Shackleton Bailey, CLA 6.307, who remarks that in this period the fact that he was several years short of the legal age for the quaestorship (30) was not a fatal objection.\n" .
